comments: Banchero (ORL) moves alongside Murray's (ATL) path and maintains a legal guarding position as incidental contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) brings his arm toward the loose ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Okongwu's (ATL) arm during the putback shot attempt.
Carter Jr. (ORL) makes clean contact with the ball in an attempt to deflect the loose ball away from Okongwu (ATL) during the rebound.
Carter Jr.'s (ORL) hand slides off the ball and onto Johnson's (ATL) arm, which affects Johnson's play at the basket.
Carter Jr. (ORL) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and then his arm slightly extends as he releases away towards the basket.
Okongwu (ATL) and Carter Jr. (ORL) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs off-ball.

Johnson (ATL) brings his arm toward the ball and marginal contact occurs as he lightly brushes Fultz's (ORL) head during the driving shot attempt.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Suggs (ORL) extends toward Young's (ATL) path and makes contact with his body, which affects Young's SQBR.
Suggs (ORL) goes to, not through, Murray (ATL) and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the same spot during the drive.
Okongwu (ATL) jumps into and initiates body contact with Suggs (ORL) that affects his shot attempt near the rim.
Bey (ATL) avoids contact with Banchero's (ORL) arm during his contest of the driving shot attempt.
Young (ATL) swipes down and initiates contact with Suggs' (ORL) face, prior to the contact with the ball during his steal attempt.
The replay center confirms the ruling on the court of Young (ATL) initiating illegal contact with Carter Jr.'s (ORL) arm,  prior to the shot clock expiring.
Okeke (ORL) initiates contact to Young's (ATL) front that affects his SQBR during the drive.
Suggs (ORL) establishes himself in Johnson's (ATL) path and absorbs the marginal contact during the pick.
Fultz (ORL) is moving alongside Murray's (ATL) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together at the end of the drive.
Fultz (ORL) legally contests Murray's (ATL) jump shot attempt.
